## log-mcp — Dual-Storage Architecture

### What Gets Logged (All 8 Categories)
| Category | Source | Retention |
|---|---|---|
| `tool_call` | Every MCP server (interceptor) | 7 years |
| `event` | Event Bus subscriber | 7 years |
| `external_api` | Every bridge server | 7 years |
| `auth` | `auth-mcp` | 7 years |
| `financial` | `escrow-mcp`, `payments-mcp` | 7 years |
| `admin_action` | `admin-mcp` | 7 years |
| `system_health` | All servers (heartbeat) | 90 days |
| `security` | Gateway + all servers | 7 years |

### Dual-Storage Architecture
- **Hot storage (0–90 days):** PostgreSQL append-only tables, partitioned by month. Indexed for fast search by `user_id`, `server`, `category`, `created_at`. Used for real-time monitoring and recent audit queries.
- **Cold storage (90 days – 7 years):** Compressed, AES-256 encrypted monthly archive files in S3 (Supabase Storage or AWS S3 Glacier). Each archive is signed with SHA-256; signature stored separately.
- **Real-time stream:** Critical log categories (`financial`, `security`, `admin_action`) also streamed to Datadog/Sentry for real-time alerting.

### Hash Chain Immutability
- Each entry has `prev_hash` (SHA-256 of previous entry) and `entry_hash` (SHA-256 of this entry's content + `prev_hash`).
- Monthly archive files are signed; signature stored separately.
- Any break in the hash chain triggers an immediate **CRITICAL** alert to the security team.
- Log deletion requires: documented compliance process + Super Admin + Legal approval. No exceptions.

### log-mcp Tools
`search_logs`, `get_entity_history`, `get_user_activity`, `export_compliance`, `verify_integrity`, `get_system_health_log`

