## Resilience Patterns (All Servers)

Every MCP server must implement all of the following:

| Pattern | Rule |
|---|---|
| **Circuit Breaker** | All external calls: 5 consecutive failures → circuit opens for 30 seconds |
| **Retry with Backoff** | Transient failures: 3 retries, base 1s, max 60s, with jitter |
| **Bulkhead Isolation** | Critical paths (payments, auctions) isolated from non-critical (analytics, notifications) |
| **Graceful Degradation** | Non-critical service failure → reduced functionality + user notification; never crash |
| **Rate Limiting** | Enforced per user, per IP, per endpoint at the Gateway level |
| **Dead Letter Queue** | Failed events after 3 retries → DLQ per server for manual inspection |

### Failure Mode Handling
| Scenario | Auto Recovery |
|---|---|
| Single MCP server crash | Container auto-restart (< 30s) |
| DB connection loss | Connection pool retry + circuit breaker |
| Redis failure | Sentinel auto-failover to replica |
| External bridge failure | Circuit breaker + fallback bridge |
| Event bus backlog | Auto-scaling consumer workers |
| Complete region failure | DNS failover to secondary region |
| Hash chain break | Immediate CRITICAL alert + point-in-time WAL recovery |

