## Deployment Architecture

| Component | Hosting | Scaling | Deploy Method |
|---|---|---|---|
| Web frontend (Next.js) | Vercel | Edge auto-scale | Git push → Vercel CI |
| MCP servers (21 local) | Railway / Render | Horizontal auto-scale per server | Docker containers, CI/CD |
| MCP bridges (13 external) | Railway / Render | Horizontal auto-scale per bridge | Docker containers, CI/CD |
| Database | Supabase Cloud | Managed | Supabase managed |
| Redis | Upstash | Serverless auto-scale | Upstash managed |
| Object storage | Supabase Storage | Unlimited (S3-backed) | Supabase managed |

### Docker — MCP Server Container
All MCP servers use the same multi-stage `Dockerfile.mcp-server` base (node:20-alpine). Each server is a separate container image. Never bundle multiple servers into one container.

### CI/CD Pipeline (Must Follow)
1. Developer pushes to feature branch.
2. GitHub Actions runs: lint → typecheck → unit tests → integration tests.
3. PR approved + merged to `main` → staging deployment triggered.
4. Staging runs E2E tests against live staging MCP servers.
5. All green → production deployment via **blue-green strategy**.
6. Health checks confirm all MCP servers responding (< 200ms p95).
7. If health check fails → **automatic rollback** to previous version.

Never deploy to production without passing all staging E2E tests. Never skip health check rollback.

### Monitoring Stack
| Tool | Monitors | Alert Threshold |
|---|---|---|
| Datadog APM | MCP server response times, error rates | p95 > 500ms, error rate > 1% |
| Sentry | Exceptions, stack traces | New error type, spike |
| `log-mcp` | Business audit, financial, security events | Any financial/security anomaly |
| UptimeRobot | Endpoint availability, SSL | Any server unreachable > 60s |
